# Story 3.4: Enable Train Selection

## Story Metadata
- **Epic:** 3 - Map & Fleet Visualization
- **Status:** done
- **Implemented:** 2025-12-28
- **Session:** SESSION-004

## User Story
As **Diana (Dispatcher)**,
I want **to click a train marker and see details**,
So that **I can investigate specific trains**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status |
|----|----------|--------|
| AC1 | Click train marker opens popup | PASS |
| AC2 | Popup shows train ID, fleet, km | PASS |
| AC3 | Popup has link to allocation view | PASS |
| AC4 | Only one popup open at a time | PASS |

## Implementation Details

### Popup Content
```typescript
const popupContent = `
  <div class="train-popup">
    <h3>Train ${train.trainId}</h3>
    <p>Fleet: ${train.fleet.name}</p>
    <p>Current km: ${train.currentKm.toLocaleString()}</p>
    <p>Status: ${train.fitnessStatus}</p>
    <a href="/allocation?train=${train.id}">View in Allocation</a>
  </div>
`;
```

### Interaction
- Click opens popup
- Click elsewhere closes popup
- Popup positioned above marker

## Dev Notes
Train selection enables Diana to investigate outliers.
Links to allocation view support workflow continuity.

